This paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum landmark set in a grid graph, which is a problem related to discrete mathematics, graph theory, and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the problem involves optimization and cost minimization, which could fall under cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
